Introduction 

Python is Object Oriented, High Level Programming Language created by Guido van Rossum during 1985- 1990. It is easy to learn, easy to read, easy to maintain, Portable, Extendable and Scalable.

To get start with Programming part you need to setup environment by downloading the latest release from the official website https://www.python.org/ and installing it. 

To Install just run the downloaded file, an Installation wizard will open. Accept all the default settings, wait until the install is finished and you are done.

Search for Python on windows search option and open IDLE to work with technical/coding part.

